servings: 2
time required: 40 minutes
---

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Keep the @butter{20%g}(for the sauce) in the fridge.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop the chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve any thick broccoli stems lengthways.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1/2%bunch}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Cut the @medium tomato{1}(cut into 1cm chunks).

Season the @British pork loin steaks{2} with salt and pepper on both sides.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the pork steaks. Fry until browned, ~{2-3%minutes} on each side. Reduce the heat to medium and fry for an additional ~{4-6%minutes}, turning every couple of mins.

Once cooked, remove to a #plate{} and cover with another plate or #foil{} to rest.

> IMPORTANT: The pork is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the potatoes have ~{10%minutes} left, pop the @Tenderstem® broccoli{150%g} onto another baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on the middle shelf until tender and crispy, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, wipe out the (now empty) frying pan and pop back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the shallot and cook until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the tomatoes and garlic, then cook until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}, then pour in the @red wine vinegar{24%ml} and allow to evaporate.

Stir the @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @sugar{1.5%tsp} and @water{75%ml}(for the sauce) into the frying pan. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat slightly and simmer until reduced by half, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once reduced, remove the sauce from the heat and vigorously stir in the cold butter until combined.

Stir through the parsley. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

When everything's ready, slice the pork steaks widthways into 2cm thick slices.

Transfer the pork to your plates and spoon over the agrodolce sauce.

Share the roasted potatoes and Tenderstem® alongside. Enjoy!